oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Up Against The Wall Redneck Mother - Bobby Bare performance - 1975-08
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Performance of Up Against The Wall Redneck Mother, written by Ray Wylie Hubbard, produced by Bill Rice and Bobby Bare, recorded in August 1975 at RCA Victor Studio in Nashville, Tenn., and performed by Bobby Bare. Most likely commercial recording (RCA Victor PB-10556 and RCA Victor APL1-1222).
